AB  - Background: Postoperative delirium (POD) is a common complication in elderly patients undergoing total hip arthroplasty (THA). This study aimed to identify risk factors for POD in this population. Methods: A prospective cohort study of 450 patients aged ≥65 years undergoing primary THA. POD was assessed using the Confusion Assessment Method (CAM). Results: POD occurred in 68 patients (15.1%). Multivariate analysis identified advanced age (OR 1.08, 95% CI 1.03-1.14), preoperative cognitive impairment (OR 3.2, 95% CI 1.8-5.7), and surgery duration >120 minutes (OR 2.4, 95% CI 1.3-4.5) as independent risk factors. Conclusions: Advanced age, cognitive impairment, and prolonged surgery are significant risk factors for POD after THA in elderly patients.
