AB  - Objective: To develop a risk prediction model for postoperative delirium (POD) in older adults undergoing total knee arthroplasty (TKA). Methods: Retrospective cohort study of 623 patients ≥65 years who underwent primary TKA. POD was diagnosed using DSM-5 criteria. Results: POD incidence was 12.4% (77/623). Independent predictors included age ≥75 years (OR 2.1, 95% CI 1.2-3.6), ASA score ≥3 (OR 2.8, 95% CI 1.5-5.2), preoperative benzodiazepine use (OR 3.5, 95% CI 1.8-6.9), and general anesthesia (OR 1.9, 95% CI 1.1-3.3). Conclusion: Several preoperative factors can help identify high-risk patients for POD prevention strategies.
